race.comment: It looks the right race for RAIKOKE (4). He won very well in quick time two back at Sandown Hillside before an even effort last time when fading late behind the talented King Zephyr. That's strong form and he gets in beautifully with 55kg from barrier three. Should lead and go very close. REGAL AZMON (1) was quite good at huge odds first up at Flemington in a bunched finish. Slight rise in trip will suit but 60kg is a bit of a leveller. APULIA (2) resumes off nearly a year. This trip will be short of his best having missed a nose in a Victoria Derby as a 3yo but he did flash home over 1500m in this race last year to grab second with 60kg. He'll be charging late. ENNA'S DREAM (7) is racing consistently in easier company but this isn't an overly deep race and she should run well. ANOTHER PROPHET (3) hasn't fired a shot since her G1 Thousand Guineas win over a year ago but this is easier.
